are%20getting%20government%20employees%20to%20use%20your%20products%2C%20it%20increases%20the%20odds%20that%20you%20will%20be%20one%20of%20the%20survivors%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20might%20have%20a%20similar%20deal%20in%20the%20offing.%20Earlier%20this%20month%2C%20US%20General%20Services%20Administration%20added%20the%20tech%20giant's%20Gemini%20model%20to%20a%20list%20of%20approved%20AI%20vendors.%20After%20that%20announcement%2C%20OpenAI%20and%20Anthropic%2C%20which%20were%20also%20added%20to%20the%20list%2C%20announced%20their%20%241%20per%20agency%20agreements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E's%20xAi%20was%20originally%20going%20to%20strike%20a%20similar%20partnership%2C%20but%20those%20talks%20fizzled%20out%20after%20Grok%20began%20posting%20antisemitic%20content%2C%20Wired%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20employees%20will%20have%20other%20avenues%20to%20use%20popular%20AI%20chatbots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20the%20US%20General%20Services%20Administration%20unveiled%20USAi%2C%20a%20secure%20platform%20where%20federal%20employees%20can%20experiment%20with%20AI%20models%20at%20no%20cost%20to%20them.%20The%20platform%20will%20initially%20feature%20models%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Meta%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Amazon%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20and%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20GSA%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20Anthropic%20and%20OpenAI's%20nominal%20fee%20agreements%20%26quot%3Bare%20not%20the%20same%20as%20the%20USAi%20access%20mechanism.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20partnerships%20follow%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20unveiling%20of%20his%20AI%20action%20plan%2C%20a%20series%20of%20policies%20designed%20to%20keep%20the%20US%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20global%20AI%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20companies%20take%20maintaining%20the%20US's%20position%20seriously.%20Last%20year%2C%20Anduril%20and%20Palantir%20announced%20their%20own%20effort%20to%20outfit%20the%20government%20with%20AI.%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20joined%20Trump%20in%20January%20to%20announce%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-stargate-project-moat-deepseek-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStargate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20%24500%20billion%20project%20that%20would%20help%20rebuild%20the%20AI%20giant's%20moat%20against%20Chinese%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic's%20agreement%20also%20applies%20to%20all%20three%20branches%2C%20underlining%20that%20the%20deal%20extends%20to%20congressional%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20repeated%20efforts%2C%20Congress%20has%20been%20unable%20to%20pass%20a%20sweeping%20AI%20law.%20Most%20recently%2C%20lawmakers%20dealt%20some%20in%20the%20industry%20a%20setback%20after%20they%20stripped%20out%20a%20provision%20that%20would%20have%20imposed%20a%20decadelong%20moratorium%20on%20state-level%20AI%20laws%20from%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-trump-big-beautiful-bill-impacts-wallet-taxes-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBig%20Beautiful%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Its%20initial%20inclusion%20sparked%20bipartisan%20opposition.%20OpenAI%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20Alphabet%20have%20all%20opposed%20previous%20state-level%20efforts%20to%20regulate%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported%2C%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawmakers-who-dont-use-ai-chatgpt-grok-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elawmakers%20remain%20skeptical%20of%20using%20AI%20chatbots%3C%2Fa%3E%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-anthropic-1-dollar-deal-trump-ai-2025-81%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%