20that%20efficiency%2C%20power%2C%20and%20looks%20were%20not%20mutually%20exclusive%20pillars%20to%20achieve.%20The%20result%20was%20designing%20a%20fast%20and%20zingy%20electric%20sports%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-roadster-what-fans-should-know-electric-vehicles-cars-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20Roadster%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20thrust%20itself%20to%2060%20miles%20per%20hour%20in%20just%203.7%20seconds%20and%20had%20a%20range%20of%20244%20miles.%20It%20could%20go%20further%20than%20other%20EVs%20at%20the%20time%2C%20squashing%20the%20Nissan%20Leaf's%2073-mile%20range%20and%20the%20Mitsubishi%20i-Miev's%2062-mile%20estimate.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20it%20didn't%20look%20or%20feel%20like%20anything%20electric%20on%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20numbers%20only%20tell%20part%20of%20the%20story.%20On%20the%20road%2C%20it%20was%20completely%20different%20from%20anything%20I've%20ever%20driven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227744b3d4-018c-40fb-a54c-58622f8d144e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBack%20to%20Tesla's%20roots%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20in%20California%20last%20summer%2C%20my%20friend%20Wade%20Higgins%20asked%20me%20if%20I%20would%20like%20to%20drive%20his%20Tesla%20Roadster.%20Naturally%2C%20I%20cleared%20out%20my%20calendar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWade%20worked%20at%20Tesla%20from%202013%20to%202015.%20In%202014%2C%20he%20sold%20some%20of%20his%20Tesla%20stock%20and%20picked%20up%20a%20used%20Roadster%20he%20found%20online.%20Wade%20estimates%20his%20Roadster%20could%20be%20worth%20three%20times%20what%20he%20originally%20paid%2C%20which%20was%20%2455K.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-political-beliefs-public-stances-timeline-republican-desantis-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk's%20polarizing%20right-wing%20presence%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20small%20number%20of%20used%20Roadsters%20on%20the%20market%2C%20current%20values%20remain%20uncertain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2219d8e194-0169-49ff-9316-32ed874b839b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20design%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20reached%20Wade's%20house%2C%20the%20doors%20from%20his%20garage%20lifted%2C%20and%20the%20silver%202008%20Roadster%20was%20unsheathed.%20I%20had%20only%20seen%20one%20on%20the%20road%20prior%2C%20so%20merely%20being%20in%20its%20presence%20was%20a%20surreal%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20thing%20I%20noticed%20was%20that%20the%20Roadster%20was%20tiny%20%E2%80%94%20its%20hood%20barely%20made%20it%20up%20to%20my%20knees.%20The%20Roadster%20was%20so%20small%20because%20it%20was%20based%20on%20the%20Lotus%20Elise%20platform.%20While%20many%20newer%20EVs%20are%20built%20from%20the%20ground%20up%20on%20electric%20platforms%2C%20Tesla%20didn't%20have%20the%20resources%20back%20in%20the%20old%20days%20to%20do%20so.%20Therefore%2C%20Tesla%20partnered%20with%20the%20then-struggling%20Lotus%20Cars%20to%20procure%20the%20vehicle's%20chassis%20and%20help%20with%20engineering%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20is%20a%20155.1-inch-long%20car%20measuring%20only%2044.4%20inches%20in%20height.%20For%20comparison%2C%20it's%20about%2030.7%20inches%20shorter%20than%20a%20Model%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f0d968ed-78bb-42c8-8b11-528e5df92fbe%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20small%20form%20factor%20is%20excellent%20for%20its%20electric%20powertrain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAerodynamics%20are%20key%20to%20securing%20the%20range.%20Simply%20put%2C%20a%20smaller%20car%20means%20a%20smaller%20frontal%20area.%20Less%20area%20means%20the%20vehicle%20won't%20have%20to%20push%20as%20much%20air%20out%20of%20the%20way%20when%20driving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20car%20also%20uses%20a%20relatively%20small%20battery.%20Its%2053-kilowatt-hour%20battery%20pack%20allows%20it%20to%20achieve%20its%20244-mile%20range.%20A%20smaller%20battery%20means%20less%20weight%20and%20fewer%20battery%20cells%20to%20keep%20cool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWade's%20Roadster%20is%20also%20still%20on%20its%20original%20battery%20pack%2C%20which%2C%20seventeen%20years%20later%2C%20is%20still%20operating%20normally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202008%20Roadster%20weighs%20about%202%2C900%20pounds.%20The%20low%20weight%20means%20the%20car%20doesn't%20need%20mountains%20of%20horsepower%20to%20go%20fast.%20The%20original%20Roadster%20%26quot%3Bonly%26quot%3B%20made%20248%20horsepower%2C%20which%20is%20far%20lower%20than%20most%20modern%20sporty%20EVs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221911b9ef-842f-44d0-b5be-65e1afdbf41a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20feel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22two%20seats%20in%20a%202008%20Tesla%20Roadster%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689f8a38194a2d49b8aeac6c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20two%20seats%20in%20the%20Roadster.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lambrecht%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tight%20dimensions%20become%20immediately%20apparent%20when%20you%20get%20behind%20the%20driver's%20seat.%20Everything%20feels%20miniature.%20You'll%20literally%20sit%20shoulder-to-shoulder%20with%20the%20passenger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarting%20the%20Roadster%20is%20also%20different%20from%20any%20other%20modern%20Tesla.%20There's%20no%20app%20or%20sleek%20keycard%20%E2%80%94%20instead%2C%20owners%20have%20a%20physical%20key.%20Slide%20it%20into%20the%20receptacle%20to%20the%20right%20of%20the%20wheel%2C%20twist%20it%2C%20and%20you'll%20hear%20a%20muted%20electronic%20hum%2C%20an%20analog%20ritual%20for%20an%20electric%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20attribute%20the%20Roadster%20shares%20with%20modern%20Teslas%20is%20the%20minimalist%20%26quot%3BTESLA%26quot%3B%20typeface%20across%20the%20rear.%20Beneath%20its%20sleek%20exterior%2C%20a%20brutal%20and%20raw%20sports%20car%20resides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f7f775f9-3d07-4adb-80b0-18fa377bbd13%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnother%20interesting%20quirk%3F%20There's%20no%20power%20steering.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20steering%20wheel%20of%20a%202008%20Tesla%20Roadster%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689f89ec194a2d49b8aeac5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20steering%20wheel.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lambrecht%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20low%20speeds%2C%20the%20driver%20receives%20a%20complimentary%20bicep%20workout.%20Especially%20when%20navigating%20through%20parking%20lots%2C%20you%20must%20supply%20a%20decent%20amount%20of%20force%20to%20make%20the%20car%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20power%20steering%20also%20means%20there's%20no%20intermediary%20between%20the%20road%20and%20the%20steering%20column.%20Every%20bump%2C%20crack%2C%20and%20imperfection%20in%20the%20asphalt's%20surface%20permeates%20up%20the%20steering%20rack%20and%20into%20your%20fingertips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ride%20is%20just%20as%20unforgiving.%20The%20taught%20suspension%20transfers%20shocks%20directly%20into%20the%20cabin%2C%20creating%20a%20bumpy%20but%20visceral%20driving%20experience.%20Every%20jolt%20and%20vibration%20reminds%20you%20that%20comfort%20was%20never%20a%20priority%20in%20the%20Roadster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20these%20attributes%20deliver%20a%20raw%20and%20engaging%20ride.%20It%20was%20truly%20one%20of%20the%20most%20fun%20EVs%20I've%20driven%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20but%20I%20could%20assume%20the%20harshness%20would%20get%20old%20if%20I%20drove%20this%20car%20frequently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a07e420e-a0eb-4a46-9ca5-9a6681bbdf99%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECharging%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Roadster%20can't%20use%20Superchargers%20because%20it%20launched%20four%20years%20before%20the%20first%20one%20was%20built.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20cannot%20DC%20fast%20charge%2C%20meaning%20you're%20limited%20to%20slower%20AC%20charging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20the%20Roadster%20will%20charge%20at%2070%20amps%2C%20which%20is%20high%20even%20for%20today's%20standards.%20Most%20EVs%20top%20out%20at%2040%20or%2048%20amps.%20This%20means%20the%20Tesla%20Roadster%20can%20charge%20at%2015.4%20kilowatts%2C%20adding%20about%2060%20miles%20of%20range%20per%20hour.%20A%20zero-to-full%20charge%20takes%20three%20and%20a%20half%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20charging%20the%20Roadster%20adds%20some%20complexity.%20It%20uses%20an%20obsolete%20charging%20connector%2C%20so%20a%20regular%20Tesla%20NACS%20connector%20won't%20work.%20You'll%20need%20an%20adapter%20if%20you%20want%20to%20charge%20on%20a%20public%20level%202%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22902c6fbd-62fd-49e8-bb90-369fd9b0851b%5C%22%3EThe%20Tesla%20Roadster%20wasn't%20made%20to%20be%20a%20mass-market%20vehicle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Roadster%20was%20made%20to%20show%20the%20world%20what%20electric%20cars%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%2017%20years%20old%2C%20the%20Tesla%20Roadster%20still%20breaks%20many%20preconceptions.%20It's%20lightweight%2C%20blisteringly%20quick%2C%20and%20still%20running%20strong%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20long-lasting%20battery%20pack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20hadn't%20been%20for%20the%20Roadster%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-is-at-a-tipping-point-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETesla%20would%20likely%20not%20be%20where%20it%20is%20today%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20think%20it's%20the%20most%20important%20car%20of%20the%202000s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freview-original-2008-tesla-roadster-most-important-car-2000s-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755507901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689f8a75a17a8c5b4