5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-playlists-music-discovery-release-radar-layoffs-cost-cutting-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESpotify%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20said%20it%20wants%20advertising%20to%20make%20up%2020%25%20of%20its%20overall%20revenue.%20As%20of%20June%2C%20that%20figure%20stood%20at%2011%25%20%E2%80%94%20a%20share%20that%20has%20barely%20budged%20over%20time.%20Second-quarter%20ad%20revenue%20was%20down%200.7%25%20versus%20the%20prior%20year%2C%20and%20media%20industry%20analyst%20Brian%20Wieser%20pondered%20in%20a%20recent%20note%20to%20clients%20whether%20it%20had%20plateaued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Camacho%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20ad%20agency%20Cheil%20UK%2C%20said%20cracks%20in%20Spotify's%20ad%20business%20have%20been%20visible%20for%20some%20time.%20That%20contrasts%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20company's%20relatively%20strong%20performance%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.spotify.com%2F2025-07-29%2Fspotify-reports-second-quarter-2025-earnings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthy%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20user%20numbers%20and%20overall%20revenue%2C%20and%20a%20stock%20price%20that's%20up%20over%20100%25%20in%20the%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20world%20demanding%20seamless%20media%20execution%20and%20measurable%20impact%2C%20Spotify%20has%20struggled%20to%20connect%20ambition%20with%20action%2C%26quot%3B%20Camacho%20said%20of%20the%20company's%20ad%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20needs%20to%20give%20brands%20access%20to%20cultural%20moments%2C%20not%20just%20audio%20slots%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThat%20means%20better%20content%20partnerships%2C%20richer%20storytelling%20formats%2C%20and%20measurement%20that%20proves%20value%20beyond%20listens.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndustry%20insiders%20say%20Spotify's%20ad%20efforts%20have%20been%20hampered%20by%20the%20company's%20focus%20on%20its%20subscription%20business%2C%20which%20is%20much%20more%20lucrative.%20Two%20ad%20buyers%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Spotify's%20customer%20service%20has%20slipped%20recently%2C%20while%20podcast%20industry%20insiders%20said%20its%20ad%20rates%20remain%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpotify%20seems%20to%20recognize%20the%20need%20for%20change.%20Longtime%20ad%20head%20Lee%20Brown%20left%20last%20month%2C%20and%20the%20company%20confirmed%20that%20a%20search%20is%20underway%20for%20a%20new%20leader.%20Ek%20appeared%20to%20blame%20Brown%20for%20Spotify's%20ad%20struggles%2C%20saying%20on%20the%20earnings%20call%20that%20%26quot%3Bexecution%26quot%3B%20and%20not%20strategy%20led%20to%20the%20poor%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20felt%20it%20was%20the%20right%20time%20for%20a%20leadership%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Ek%20added.%20Brown%2C%20who%20recently%20became%20the%20chief%20revenue%20officer%20at%20DoorDash%2C%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpotify's%20executives%20said%20on%20the%20recent%20earnings%20call%20that%20they%20want%20advertising%20to%20contribute%20more%20to%20the%20company's%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f8ca87d7-918f-4d11-b8d6-8df6df46d96c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPodcasts%20offer%20advertisers%20access%20to%20Spotify's%20Premium%20users%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20strategy%20has%20been%20messy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20ways%2C%20Spotify%20has%20a%20business%20model%20that%20eats%20its%20own%20tail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Spotify%20converts%20too%20many%20free%20users%20into%20Premium%20subscribers%2C%20the%20audience%20for%20advertisers%20shrinks.%20If%20it%20makes%20the%20free%20offering%20too%20attractive%2C%20users%20won't%20be%20tempted%20to%20upgrade.%20Spotify's%20ad-supported%20tier%20serves%20as%20an%20important%20on-ramp%20for%20its%20Premium%20business%20%E2%80%94%20plus%20the%20%241.9%20billion%20in%20ad%20sales%20it%20brought%20in%20last%20year%20helps%20toward%20paying%20its%20substantial%20royalties%20to%20music%20labels%20and%20other%20content%20creators.%20However%2C%20Premium%20is%20the%20sacred%20cash%20cow%3A%20Enders%20Analysis%20estimates%20that%20gross%20profits%20for%20Premium%20are%20around%2015%20to%2020%20times%20those%20of%20the%20advertising%20tier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-gimlet-boss-says-spotify-lit-money-fire-celebrity-podcasts-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebig%20push%20into%20podcasts%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20have%20ads%20for%20those%20on%20the%20Premium%20tier%20%E2%80%94%20offered%20a%20way%20to%20bridge%20that%20gap.%20It%20also%20gave%20advertisers%20the%20chance%20to%20reach%20more%20affluent%20audiences.%20Spotify%20spent%20more%20than%20%241%20billion%20to%20acquire%20companies%20like%20Gimlet%20Media%20and%20Anchor%2C%20and%20signed%20exclusive%20deals%20with%20Joe%20Rogan%20and%20the%20Obamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Joe%20Rogan%20speaking%20into%20a%20mic.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63647667ff27460018ed8e13%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJoe%20Rogan%20walks%20back%20on%20his%20claim%20that%20schools%20were%20putting%20out%20cat%20litter%20for%20kids%20who%20are%20'furries.'%3Cp%3EVivian%20Zink%2FSyfy%2FNBCU%20Photo%20Bank%2FNBCUniversal%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPodcast%20executives%20and%20ad%20buyers%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20podcast%20advertising%20strategy%20has%20been%20messy%2C%20with%20several%20pivots%20in%20its%20few%20years%20of%20operation.%20Spotify%20ended%20some%20of%20its%20original%20and%20exclusive%20programming%2C%20cut%20staff%2C%20flip-flopped%20its%20stance%20on%20areas%20like%20measurement%20and%20ad%20pricing%20floors%2C%20and%20made%20a%20pivot%20to%20video%20that%20is%20still%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20and%20has%20yet%20to%20prove%20itself%20as%20a%20guaranteed%20moneymaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpotify%20acquired%20the%20podcast%20hosting%20and%20adtech%20company%20Megaphone%20in%202020%20in%20a%20%24235%20million%20deal%20that%20was%20designed%20to%20help%20podcast%20publishers%20make%20more%20money%20through%20its%20advertising%20marketplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20hiccups%20from%20the%20start.%20A%20former%20Spotify%20ad%20sales%20exec%20said%20there%20was%20an%20irony%20in%20the%20company%20attempting%20to%20sell%20Megaphone%20to%20podcasters%20as%20a%20best-in-class%20adtech%20solution%20while%20Spotify%20itself%20uses%20Google%20as%20its%20ad%20server.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20podcast%20publisher%20said%20they%20were%20getting%20around%20%248%20or%20%249%20CPMs%20%E2%80%94%20the%20cost%20of%201%2C000%20impressions%20for%20a%20digital%20ad%20%E2%80%94%20on%20average%20through%20Megaphone%2C%20versus%20the%20%2420%20to%20%2440%20CPMs%20they%20would%20achieve%20for%20host-read%20ads.%20However%2C%20they%20acknowledged%20that%20directly%20sold%20ads%20usually%20fetch%20higher%20prices%20than%20those%20sold%20via%20third-party%20adtech%2C%20such%20as%20Spotify's.%20The%20average%20CPM%20price%20advertisers%20paid%20for%20digital%20audio%20ads%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%20this%20year%20was%20%2416.51%2C%20according%20to%20the%20analytics%20company%20Measured%20%E2%80%94%20though%20the%20final%20fee%20a%20podcast%20publisher%20would%20receive%20after%20platforms%20and%20other%20third%20parties%20take%20their%20cut%20would%20be%20smaller.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Spotify%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20average%20CPM%20on%20Spotify%20is%20%26quot%3Bfar%20above%26quot%3B%20%249%2C%20though%20they%20declined%20to%20provide%20additional%20specifics.%20They%20said%20that%20ad%20revenue%20is%20influenced%20by%20macroeconomic%20and%20seasonal%20shifts%20that%20may%20impact%20overall%20CPMs.%20Publisher%20revenue%20generated%20through%20the%20Spotify%20Audience%20Network%20had%20seen%20double-digit%20growth%20year-over-year%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225b473976-9229-49a3-b0b8-a3649d1c1e74%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20pivot%20to%20video%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESpotify%20has%20been%20introducing%20other%20money-making%20opportunities%20to%20offset%20volatile%20ad%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20as%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-video-podcasts-creators-youtube-comparison-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20big%20video%20push%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20launched%20the%20Spotify%20Partner%20Program%2C%20offering%20creators%20a%2050%25%20share%20of%20the%20ad%20revenue%20their%20videos%20generate.%20It%20has%20encouraged%20some%20publishers%20and%20creators%20to%20get%20on%20board%20by%20giving%20them%20minimum%20revenue%20guarantees%2C%20though%20it's%20unclear%20how%20long%20those%20will%20last.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225712%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Spotify%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6786b9b7e294a7514e8d151d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELast%20year%2C%20Spotify%20held%20an%20event%20for%20creators%20about%20tools%20and%20new%20features.%3Cp%3EAmanda%20Perelli%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Spotify%20Partner%20Program%20has%20been%20a%20%26quot%3Bbig%20win%26quot%3B%20for%20YMH%20Studios%2C%20producer%20of%20podcasts%20including%20%26quot%3BYour%20Mom's%20House%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3B2%20Bears%2C%201%20Cave%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20company's%20head%20of%20ad%20revenue%2C%20Alan%20Abdine.%20He%20said%20the%20company%20had%20seen%20a%20consistent%2020%25%20to%2030%25%20revenue%20lift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20ad%20buyers%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Spotify%20must%20prove%20it%20can%20be%20a%20meaningful%20player%20in%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVideo%20here%20feels%20like%20an%20add-on%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheil's%20Camacho%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20Spotify%20wants%20to%20be%20bold%2C%20brave%2C%20and%20first%2C%20it%20needs%20to%20reinvent%20what%20video%20within%20an%20audio%20experience%20could%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Spotify%20spokesperson%20said%20video%20podcast%20consumption%20is%20up%2054%25%20this%20year%2C%20with%20users%20who%20watch%20a%20podcast%20consuming%201.5%20times%20as%20much%20as%20those%20who%20just%20listen.%20The%20spokesperson%20said%20it%20is%20building%20ways%20to%20improve%20the%20creative%20options%20available%20for%20creators%2C%20fans%2C%20and%20advertisers%2C%20such%20as%20audio-to-video%20playback%2C%20built-in%20community%20tools%2C%20better%20on-platform%20analytics%2C%20and%20new%20monetization%20models%20like%20the%20Spotify%20Partner%20Program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f3b08544-efe9-406c-9a83-8727fbfda69e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECustomer%20service%20takes%20a%20slide%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20advertisers%20have%20been%20put%20off%20by%20Spotify's%20increasing%20focus%20on%20automated%20ad%20buying%20and%20by%20high%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-makes-key-new-ad-hire-poaching-from-spotify-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eturnover%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20company's%20ad%20sales%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-lay-off-relocated-abroad-forced-leave-country-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpotify%20cut%202%2C300%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-employees-question-lavish-spending-events-amid-big-layoffs-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree%20rounds%20of%20layoffs%20in%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Last%20year%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadage.com%2Farticle%2Fdigital-marketing-ad-tech-news%2Fspotify-focus-smaller-clients-programmatic-ad-tech-includes-40-layoffs%2F2569771%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaxed%3C%2Fa%3E%2040%20positions%20and%2017%20open%20roles%20in%20its%20ad%20and%20campaign%20management%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20Granger%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20audio%20ad%20agency%20Oxford%20Road%2C%20said%20getting%20a%20response%20from%20the%20Spotify%20team%20could%20take%20days%20versus%20a%20matter%20of%20hours%20from%20other%20partners%2C%20and%20that%20many%20of%20its%20accounts%20were%20handled%20offshore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Spotify%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20prides%20itself%20on%20its%20customer%20service%20and%20aims%20to%20respond%20to%20advertisers%20within%20three%20to%20six%20hours%2C%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20resolving%20any%20issues%20or%20queries%20within%2048%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGranger%20said%20his%20agency%20had%20experienced%20consistency%20issues%20when%20Spotify%20inserted%20ads%20into%20podcast%20streams.%20Sometimes%2C%20ads%20are%20clustered%20in%20a%20short%20burst%20instead%20of%20being%20paced%20evenly%2C%20eroding%20a%20campaign's%20performance.%20Ad%20prices%20had%20recently%20jumped%20without%20a%20commensurate%20increase%20in%20the%20value%20they%20delivered%2C%20Granger%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Spotify's%20measurement%20offering%20was%20%26quot%3Binhospitable%26quot%3B%20for%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20August%20note%20to%20clients%2C%20analysts%20from%20Arete%20Research%20said%20they%20questioned%20whether%20Spotify%20%26quot%3Bhas%20the%20DNA%20of%20an%20ads%20company%2C%20or%20whether%20ads%20are%20simply%20a%20way%20to%20spur%20users%20into%20paying%20for%20Premium.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20dynamic%20isn't%20lost%20on%20the%20ad%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSpotify%20just%20doesn't%20prioritize%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20advertising%20community%20the%20way%20it%20does%20that%20of%20its%20subscriber%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Granger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bc526209-89f4-4ed9-afda-c6bf342b14a9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpotify%20is%20pinning%20its%20hopes%2