ns-by-2030-in-sweeping-workforce-nationalization%2Farticleshow%2F123357599.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F123357599.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EKuwait%20aims%20to%20fully%20nationalize%20its%20judiciary%20by%202030%2C%20replacing%20foreign%20judges%20and%20staff%20with%20qualified%20Kuwaiti%20professionals.%20This%20initiative%20is%20part%20of%20broader%20reforms%20to%20empower%20local%20talent%20and%20modernize%20the%20legal%20sector.%20Similar%20national%20workforce%20integration%20efforts%20are%20underway%20in%20vital%20sectors%20like%20oil%20and%20technical%20fields%2C%20with%20stricter%20recruitment%20rules%20for%20expatriates.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fkuwait-to-replace-all-foreign-judges-with-citizens-by-2030-in-sweeping-workforce-nationalization%2Farticleshow%2F123357599.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fkuwait-to-replace-all-foreign-judges-with-citizens-by-2030-in-sweeping-workforce-nationalization%2Famp_articleshow%2F123357599.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fkuwait-to-replace-all-foreign-judges-with-citizens-by-2030-in-sweeping-workforce-nationalization%2Famp_articleshow%2F123357599.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Millennials'%20favorite%20companies%20are%20growing%20up%20or%20dying%20out%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20pushing%20a%20dolly%20of%20millennial%20pastel%20colored%20boxes%20towards%20a%20hearse%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689f7fe4cfc04e97619b83b3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJanel%20Strachan%2C%20a%2031-year-old%20New%20Yorker%2C%20loved%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fmidea-u-shaped-air-conditioner-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMidea%20air%20conditioner%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Strachan's%20techie%20boyfriend%20recommended%20the%20model%2C%20and%20she%20soon%20became%20a%20devotee.%20She%20liked%20its%20convenient%2C%20apartment-oriented%20features.%20She%20could%20easily%20use%20an%20app%20to%20turn%20it%20on%2C%20and%20its%20sleek%20design%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20her%20to%20see%20outside.%20The%20unit%2C%20which%20first%20hit%20the%20market%20in%202020%2C%20was%20acclaimed%20by%20Wirecutter%2C%20the%20reviews%20arm%20of%20The%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20and%20developed%20a%20cult%20following%20among%20a%20certain%20type%20of%20consumers%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-pink-gen-z-yellow-very-peri-orchid-flower-generational-colors-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EYounger%20adults%20who%20like%20design%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20quality%20and%20have%20enough%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-americans-spend-lower-income-cut-back-affordability-earnings-consumers-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edisposable%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20throw%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20at%20an%20air%20AC%2C%20and%20aren't%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20they%20can%20afford%20or%20finesse%20a%20home%20or%20apartment%20with%20central%20air.%20When%20her%20parents%20came%20to%20visit%20her%20apartment%2C%20they%20were%20blown%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20Midea%20is%20a%20very%20millennial%20brand.%20It%20came%20with%20a%20particular%20air%20of%20being%20in%20the%20know%2C%20through%20both%20word%20of%20mouth%20and%20the%20more%20rarified%20reader%20and%20viewership%20of%20high-profile%20recommenders%2C%20and%20modernizing%20a%20not-so-sexy%20but%20very%20necessary%20appliance.%20It's%20an%20aesthetic%20that%20has%20come%20to%20define%20the%20generation%3A%20Appealing%20packaging%2C%20digital%20word%20of%20mouth%20in%20all%20of%20the%20right%20places%2C%20and%20vaguely%20purpose-driven%20(the%20Midea%20is%20also%20known%20for%20its%20energy%20efficiency).%20But%20a%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20Midea%20owners%20got%20majorly%20in%20their%20feels%20amid%20a%20big%20yikes.%20Around%201.7%20million%20Midea%20units%20were%20recalled%20due%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20potential%20mold%20exposure.%20For%20Midea%20devotees%2C%20it%20was%20a%20recall%20heard%20around%20TikTok%2C%20X%2C%20and%2C%20yes%2C%20even%20The%20New%20York%20Times.%20The%20bad%20news%20even%20managed%20to%20reach%20my%20friend%2C%20who%20was%20traveling%20on%20a%20generally%20unplugged%20camping%20expedition%20in%20the%20Sahara%20Desert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20see%20that%20it%20got%20recalled%2C%20it%20was%20a%20big%20letdown%2C%26quot%3B%20Strachan%20says.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20hates%20when%20tech%20doesn't%20work%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20an%20air%20conditioner%20filled%20with%20mold%20is%20an%20extreme%20example%2C%20but%20the%20demographic%20it's%20tailored%20toward%20is%20having%20its%20own%20consumer%20reckoning.%20Glossier%20is%20at%20Sephora%3B%20Mideas%20are%20having%20holes%20drilled%20in%20them%3B%20their%20dentists%20can%20no%20longer%20be%20replaced%20with%20flashy%20online%20products.%20Millennials%20are%20waking%20up%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20their%20beloved%2C%20cutting-edge%2C%20never-done-before%20brands%20are%20just%20that%20%E2%80%94%20brands.%20The%20heady%20days%20of%20pastel-toned%20websites%20with%20quirky%20ad%20copy%20are%20long%20gone.%20What%20once%20seemed%20like%20a%20permanent%20move%20toward%20a%20direct%2C%20values-centered%20relationship%20with%20consumers%20has%20been%20exposed%20as%20a%20marketing%20ploy.%20The%20era%20of%20the%20trendy%20millennial%20brand%20is%20over%2C%20and%20the%20brands%20that%20have%20settled%20into%20just%20boring%20old%20retailers%20have%20emerged%20on%20top%20%E2%80%94%20another%20signpost%20that%20millennials%20have%2C%20just%20maybe%2C%20become%20old%20and%20boring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2213773a0a-f003-4319-9c44-3045d8e284e1%5C%22%3EThe%20rise%20and%20fall%20of%20the%20millennial%20brand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20turnover%20of%20generationally-associated%20trends%20and%20brands%20is%20nothing%20new.%20Throughout%20the%20decades%2C%20companies%20that%20become%20associated%20with%20one%20age%20group%20face%20struggles%20as%20they%20grow.%20Dhananjay%20Nayakankuppam%2C%20a%20marketing%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Iowa%20who%20studies%20branding%2C%20gave%20the%20example%20of%20whiskey%3A%20In%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%2C%20whiskey%20was%20the%20drink%20of%20choice%2C%20but%20within%2020%20to%2025%20years%2C%20a%20generational%20shift%20led%20to%20whiskey%20falling%20out%20of%20favor.%20Whiskey%20supplier%20Brindiamo%20said%20that%2C%20from%201970%20to%201990%2C%20bourbon%20lost%20almost%2050%25%20of%20its%20market%20share.%20The%20younger%20generation%20started%20pivoting%20toward%20wine%20and%20lighter%20alcohols%20as%20a%20healthier%20alternative.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20a%20specific%20company%2C%20he%20pointed%20to%20the%20car%20company%20Buick%2C%20which%20had%20struggled%20to%20shake%20its%20stuffy%2C%20older%20reputation%20%E2%80%94%20younger%20consumers%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20grandparent%20car%2C%20and%20eventually%20the%20older%20generations%20started%20to%20question%20if%20the%20brand%20was%20even%20for%20them%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20are%20the%20moments%20when%20brands%20can%20end%20up%20stuck%20between%20a%20rock%20and%20a%20hard%20place%2C%20Nayakankuppam%20said.%20If%20they%20market%20themselves%20as%20still%20young%20and%20cool%2C%20that%20younger%20and%20cooler%20cohort%20might%20look%20around%20and%20see%20that%20it's%20only%20their%20grandparents%20or%20parents%20consuming%20those%20goods.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20older%20audience%20might%20worry%20that%20the%20brand%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20not%20for%20them%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20brands%20which%20get%20too%20tightly%20tied%20to%20a%20particular%20cohort%20or%20a%20generation%20as%20that%20cohort%20and%20generation%20ages%2C%20it%20can%20leave%20the%20brand%20high%20and%20dry%2C%26quot%3B%20Nayakankuppam%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20things%20that%20make%20a%20brand%20quintessentially%20%26quot%3Bmillennial.%26quot%3B%20One%20of%20the%20hallmarks%20of%20the%20era%20was%20the%20direct-to-consumer%20model.%20Casper%20made%20the%20mattress%20shopping%20process%20into%20a%20seamless%20box%20at%20your%20doorstep.%20Warby%20Parker%20made%20it%20so%20that%20you%20could%20try%20on%20trendy%20tortoise-shell%20frames%20at%20home.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmiledirectclub-shutdown-bankruptcy-confuses-angers-customers-unfinished-treatments-bills-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESmileDirectClub%20would%20fix%3C%2Fa%3E%20your%20smile%20with%20invisible%20aligners%20%E2%80%94%20until%20it%20abruptly%20shut%20down%2C%20leaving%20some%20customers%20high%20and%20dry%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fag.ny.gov%2Fpress-release%2F2024%2Fattorney-general-james-recovers-48-million-consumers-wrongly-charged%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20hook%20for%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20these%20brands%20decided%20to%20move%20into%20brick-and-mortar%2C%20they%20tried%20to%20make%20the%20shopping%20experience%20more%20interactive%20or%20immersive.%20At%20clothing%20brand%20Reformation's%20stores%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20customers%20can%20pick%20out%20an%20outfit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecut.com%2F2017%2F12%2Fnew-reformation-bond-street-store.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BClueless%26quot%3B-style%20on%20a%20screen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20have%20items%20in%20different%20sizes%20and%20styles%20magically%20transport%20into%20a%20dressing%20room%20wardrobe.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glossy.co%2Ffashion%2Fthe-rise-of-the-dtc-neighborhood%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMillennial%20corridors%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20trendy%20downtown%20areas%20where%20shoppers%20could%20peruse%20goods%20straight%20from%20their%20Instagram%20ads%20%E2%80%94%20began%20to%20appear%20in%20urban%20neighborhoods%20and%20offered%20a%20sleek%2C%20fun%20shopping%20experience.%20This%20wasn't%20your%20childhood%20mall%3B%20stores%20were%20showrooms%2C%20and%20the%20products%20were%20the%20art.%20Beyond%20remaking%20the%20shelves%2C%20millennial%20brands%20made%20you%20feel%20good%20about%20consuming%3A%20You%20weren't%20just%20buying%20cloth%20slippers%20or%20hipster%20glasses%3B%20you%20were%20also%20saving%20the%20world.%20They%20were%20packaged%20in%20pastel%20fonts%20and%20winky%20innuendos%2C%20showing%20that%20you%20were%20with%20the%20times%2C%20or%20at%20least%20in%20on%20the%20ironic%20joke.%20In%20a%20world%20where%20the%20economic%20odds%20were%20stacked%20against%20millennials%2C%20these%20brands%20reasoned%2C%20why%20not%20make%20the%20essentials%20have%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20fun%3F.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20the%20generation%20they%20cater%20to%2C%20these%20brands%20have%20gone%20through%20some%20growing%20pains.%20Some%20were%20gobbled%20up%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-sells-moosejaw-bonobos-eloquii-in-post-marc-lore-era-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20established%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20others%20tried%20to%20push%20the%20limits%20of%20their%20business%20models%20and%20branch%20out%2C%20with%20varying%20degrees%20of%20success.%20The%20least%20lucky%20millennial%20brands%20shuttered%20completely%20or%20declared%20bankruptcy%2C%20unable%20to%20grow%20beyond%20th