9-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efounder%20Emily%20Weiss's%3C%2Fa%3E%20Into%20The%20Gloss%20blog.%20The%20brand%20thrived%2C%20even%20launching%20a%20%3Cem%3Egasp%3C%2Fem%3E%20physical%20location%20in%20Manhattan%20in%202018.%20But%20this%20was%20the%20millennial%20cool%20version%20of%20retail.%20Going%20to%20the%20store%20was%20more%20than%20just%20going%20out%20to%20buy%20makeup%3A%20It%20was%20a%20full%20experience.%20In%20its%20heyday%2C%20I%20would%20even%20drag%20out-of-town%20visitors%20there.%20Glossier's%20perfectly%20pink%2C%20just%20laidback-enough%20marketing%20worked%20its%20wonders%20on%20me%2C%20and%20lots%20of%20other%20devotees%3A%20Everyone%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20cool%20Glossier%20girl.%20The%20store%20was%20multiple%20stories%20tall%20and%20built%20to%20be%20Instagrammed.%20Instead%20of%20just%20grabbing%20something%20off%20the%20shelf%2C%20the%20actual%20product%20for%20sale%20was%20tucked%20away%20and%20disbursed%20via%20workers%20holding%20iPads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20seven%20years%2C%20Glossier%20has%20had%20its%20own%20ups%20and%20downs%2C%20but%20it's%20settled%20into%20a%20familiar%20rhythm%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20isn't%20as%20sexy%20as%20a%20multi-story%2C%20wonderland%20flagship.%20Instead%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20makeup%20brand%20sold%20at%20a%20national%2C%20visible%20retailer%2C%20and%20at%20its%20own%20stores.%20Now%2C%20I%20get%20my%20Glossier%20at%20Sephora%2C%20and%20the%20brand%20successfully%20capitalized%20on%20newer%20trends%3A%20Its%20%26quot%3BYou%26quot%3B%20perfume%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglossier-you-perfume-viral-tiktok-genz-millennial-saved-brand-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20Katie%20Notopoulos%20writes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saved%20Glossier%20from%20the%20proverbial%20millennial%20dustbin%20of%20irrelevance.%20That%20original%20Glossier%20store%20quietly%20closed%20in%202020%2C%20although%20another%20flagship%20rose%20back%2