%20language%20models%20to%20real-world%20applications%20are%20extremely%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Evaluable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-cofounder-greg-brockman-vibe-coding-fun-engineering-swe-quality-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBrockman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20cofounded%20OpenAI%20in%202015%2C%20added%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabridge-wants-to-buy-healthcare-ai-startups-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edomains%20like%20healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20require%20founders%20to%20think%20about%20all%20the%20stakeholders%20and%20how%20they%20can%20insert%20AI%20models%20into%20the%20existing%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20so%20much%20fruit%20that%20is%20not%20yet%20picked%2C%20so%20go%20ahead%20and%20ride%20the%20GPT%20river%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrockman%20also%20advised%20founders%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-wrapper-startup-founders-see-risks-of-openai-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20%26quot%3Bbetter%20wrappers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BAI%20wrapper%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20dismissive%20term%20used%20to%20refer%20to%20simple%20applications%20that%20are%20built%20on%20top%20of%20existing%20AI%20models%20and%20can%20be%20easily%20offered%20by%20LLM%20companies%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20about%20understanding%20a%20domain%20and%20building%20up%20expertise%20and%20relationships%20and%20all%20of%20those%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Brockman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrockman's%20comments%20are%20part%20of%20a%20Silicon%20Valley%20debate%20about%20how%20new%20AI%20founders%20can%20future-proof%20their%20startup%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-yes-man-mode-gpt5-personalities-sycophantic-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%